  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load design.md §5, spec.md FR-20, and the Spike #2 artifact in `notes/spikes/`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Inventory existing types">Glob `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/*.ts`; confirm none cover the six Compose flows. Match the file-naming + export-style of neighbors.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Author six interfaces">Create `compose-contracts.ts` with the six locked interfaces (exact names per Spike #2 artifact). Add JSDoc citing FR-20 + design.md §5 for each.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Stub receivers minimally">In `compose-contracts.ts`, export a `ComposeEventBusContract` type union so PaneEventBus can validate dispatch shapes. Receivers themselves stay in Tasks 042/043/045.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Build TypeScript">Run `npm run build` in SpaarkeAi; confirm zero errors under `strict`.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Run shared client build">Run `pwsh ./scripts/Build-AllClientComponents.ps1`.</step>
    <step order="6" name="UI test execution">Run the ui-tests defined below — the smoke harness validates type imports + a minimal render.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 041 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Component Renders">A minimal harness component that imports all six types and renders an empty Fluent v9 `Surface` — no console errors.</test>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">Harness surface renders in dark theme using semantic tokens — no hard-coded hex.</test>
    <test name="Contract Shape Validation">Compile-time assertion: each of the six interfaces is exported, has expected required fields per Spike #2, and the discriminated union `ComposeEventBusContract` covers all six.</test>
  </ui-tests>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build TypeScript (strict)</tool>
    <tool name="pwsh">Run Build-AllClientComponents.ps1</tool>
  </tools>

